        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "App bar",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>The app bar, formerly known as the action bar in Android, is a special kind of toolbar that&#x2019;s used for branding, navigation, search, and actions.</p><p>The nav icon at the left side of the app bar can be:</p><ul><li>A control to open a navigation drawer.</li><li>An up arrow for navigating upward through your app&#x2019;s hierarchy.</li><li>Omitted entirely if no navigation is required from this screen.</li></ul><p>The title in the app bar reflects the current page. It can be an app title, page title, or a page filter.</p><p>Icons on the right side of the app bar are app-related actions. The menu icon opens the overflow menu, which contains secondary actions and menu items like help, settings, and feedback.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7RTFrbmpoWjRrY00/layout_structure_appbar_structure1.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">App bar structure</div><p>On the left: Nav icon, title, and filter icon<br>On the right: Action and menu icons </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsU1FwTUx3cmRUNG8/layout_structure_appbar_structure2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Light</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsbGREMW9BdDdnSUk/layout_structure_appbar_structure3.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Dark</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsZF9VZDhtQlF5RGM/layout_structure_appbar_structure4.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Colored</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsQnFjd0tiMmtsMU0/layout_structure_appbar_structure5.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Transparent</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>In an app bar, all icons should be the same color. </p><p>The title can have a distinct color from the icons if increased visual hierarchy is needed. Distinct title colors work best on backgrounds with enough contrast for both white and black glyphs.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsbkxqbW9kQWgxZkk/layout_structure_appbar_structure6.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Single color (default)</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQselRDRFlzNkI0SFE/layout_structure_appbar_structure7.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Distinct title color</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Title color"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Default heights:</strong></p><p>Mobile Landscape: 48dp<br>Mobile Portrait: 56dp<br>Tablet/Desktop: 64dp</p><p>For extended app bars, the height is equal to the default height plus content increment(s).</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsLUFJUnFlRHVhUVU/layout_structure_appbar_metrics1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>App bar height: 56dp<br>App bar left and right padding: 16dp<br>App bar icon top, bottom, left padding: 16dp<br>App bar title left padding: 72dp<br>App bar title bottom padding: 20dp</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsSDBhX3BwSURRc1U/layout_structure_appbar_metrics3.png",
                      "caption": "<p>The app bar with significantly increased height for prominence</p><p>App bar height = 128dp</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Metrics"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsTW1zb2x5WWg5cDA/layout_structure_appbar_metrics5.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Action area height: 56dp<br>Title area height: 80dp<br>Title area bottom padding: 8dp<br>Description area height: 72dp<br>Description area bottom padding: 16dp</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsOFVmeDlPTU5LZ1E/layout_structure_appbar_metrics7.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Incremental keyline is set by the app bar height, with a height of 64dp, which determines the keyline increment.</p><p>App bar height: 64dp<br>App bar left and right content padding: 24dp<br>App bar icon top and bottom padding: 20dp</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsVm5pN2ZRWFZQV3c/layout_structure_appbar_metrics8.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Prominent app bar height: 128dp<br>App bar left and right icon padding: 24dp<br>App bar left content padding: 80dp</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Density</strong></p><p>When the mouse and keyboard are the primary input methods, measurements may be condensed to accommodate denser layouts.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3eUxkRzhYdE5CWlk/layout_structure_appbar_metrics7_dense.png",
                      "caption": "<p><strong>Dense app bar on desktop</strong></p><p>App bar height: 48dp<br>App bar left and right content padding: 24<br>App bar left content padding: 80dp<br>Icon height with touch target: 40dp</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3dlM1Y0hCLThaYmc/layout_structure_appbar_metrics8_dense.png",
                      "caption": "<p><strong>Dense prominent app bar </strong></p><p>Dense prominent app bar height: 96dp<br>App bar left and right content padding: 24dp<br>App bar left content padding: 80dp</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>A menu is a temporary sheet of paper that always overlaps the app bar, rather than behaving as an extension of the app bar.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsU094a25SRS1LXzQ/layout_structure_appbar_menu1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Example of an app bar</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsLUtFU1dySnRkbFE/layout_structure_appbar_menu2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Example of menu in an app nar</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Menus"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "System bars",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>On Android, the status bar contains notification icons and system icons. On Chrome, the top bar contains the window controls: minimize, full screen, and close. In a Chrome app, the top bar can disappear, and the window controls are then brought into the app bar. </p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsLUFLM2xkRElVM2s/layout_structure_system_status1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Android status bar</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7Tkh3MGZVVktoOTQ/layout_structure_system_status2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Chrome window bar</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Status bar/window bar"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Metrics:<br>Android status bar height: 24dp<br>Chrome window height: 32dp</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsUkFVNERQODRoakk/layout_structure_system_status3.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Android status bar on top of the app bar</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7OFZxQTM5SmxHQjA/layout_structure_system_status4.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Chrome window bar on top of the app bar </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7cHV2LWpmTnRUbm8/layout_structure_system_status5.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Chrome window controls inside app bar</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
